						               													<description>Hidden Identity game based upon &amp;quot;The Strange Case of Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Three to six players will secretly draw characters from a bag. All characters are considered &amp;quot;good citizens&amp;quot;, except for Dr. Jekyll. Then, proceeding through 6 different stories, each player will draw and play clues based on their secret character. As these clues are played on the game board, players will each take turns going on &amp;quot;holiday&amp;quot;, which will add to the suspense of determining who is good and who is hiding their real persona. All players can make accusations after successfully winning stories 4 and 5. Beware though! As Dr. Jekyll can make false accusations to further his transformation!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The good citizens are also attempting to remove chemicals (white substance cubes) from the board to thwart Dr. Jekyll's transformation. Dr. Jekyll will try to play clues of his own to eliminate the citizens and transform himself and escape forever.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Based on Robert Louis Stevenson's novella, &amp;quot;The Strange Case of Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde, explore six peculiar incidents while trying to determine who is Dr. Jekyll ...before he escapes as Mr. Hyde! This classic story is the perfect theme for a social deduction game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
